  "author": "Guru Bin — OPAL Deep Expansion 2026-03-16",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "At rest, this is a well-behaved granular pad: medium grains, low scatter, predictable. The entire performance lives in aftertouch. Pressing into any held note ramps posScatter from 0.08 toward 1.0 — the grain playhead fractures and begins firing into random positions. Press harder and pitchScatter arrives: the grains start arriving at different pitches, the chord dissolving into harmonic dust. Release pressure and the pad reassembles itself. The instrument rewards players with pressure-sensitive keyboards.",
  "tags": ["granular", "prism", "aftertouch", "scatter", "pressure", "expressive", "performance", "dynamic"],
  "macroLabels": ["CHARACTER", "MOVEMENT", "COUPLING", "SPACE"],
